sentences: The first Dvar album was released in 1995, and the last in 2021.
The first Dvar album was released in 1995, and the last in 2021.
Their first known work was a 1998 self-released tape called Raii, though rumors have circulated of an earlier self-released tape from 1995, simply named DVAR.
In 2000, the duo issued a self-released 4-track CD-R demo called Taai Liira.
In 2002, the band released their first album on the Italian S.P.K. R/Radio Luxor record label, called Piirrah.
In 2003, Dvar moved to the Russian label Irond and released five albums: Roach (2003), Rakhilim (2004), a 2004 re-release of Taai Liira with bonus tracks, Hor Hor (2005) and Oramah Maalhur (2005).

In 2003, Dvar moved to the Russian label Irond and released five albums: Roach (2003), Rakhilim (2004), a 2004 re-release of Taai Liira with bonus tracks, Hor Hor (2005) and Oramah Maalhur (2005).
The album Madegirah – Early Works was announced in 2005, but not be released until 2009.
The album Madegirah – Early Works was announced in 2005, but not be released until 2009.
In 2007, the band moved to the label Gravitator and released Jraah Mraah.
Their song "Teremiah K'ruun" was used in an Alfa-Bank 2007 New Year commercial.
In 2008, the band released Zii under the label Art Music Group.
In 2009, Fayah! was released, a dark counterpart to Zii, along with a release of Madegirah, now entitled Madegirah – Bizarre Rares and Early Works.
Physical copies of the album were released in December 2012 on Shadowplay Records.
In December 2021, after 9 years of silence, the band released their new single n'aharii on bandicamp and Spotify, announcing a new album.

Their first known work was a 1998 self-released tape called Raii, though rumors have circulated of an earlier self-released tape from 1995, simply named DVAR.
In 2003, Dvar moved to the Russian label Irond and released five albums: Roach (2003), Rakhilim (2004), a 2004 re-release of Taai Liira with bonus tracks, Hor Hor (2005) and Oramah Maalhur (2005).
Their song "Teremiah K'ruun" was used in an Alfa-Bank 2007 New Year commercial.
In 2009, Fayah! was released, a dark counterpart to Zii, along with a release of Madegirah, now entitled Madegirah – Bizarre Rares and Early Works.
In mid-2010, their tenth anniversary album, El Mariil was released, with an unusual medieval sound.
In December 2021, after 9 years of silence, the band released their new single n'aharii on bandicamp and Spotify, announcing a new album.
